  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Students having posttraumatic stress (PTSD) as defined according to a scoring
             algorithm of the Harvard Trauma Questionnaire previously described by the Harvard
             Refugee Trauma group and used in a Kosovar Albanian population. This definition of
             PTSD requires a score of 3 or 4, on a Likert scale of 1-4, on at least one of the four
             of the reexperiencing symptoms (Criterion B), at least 3 of the 7 avoidance and
             numbing symptoms (Criterion C), and at least 2 of the 5 arousal symptoms (Criterion D)
             in addition to exposure to a traumatic event (Criterion A).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  No specific exclusion criteria. Students having PTSD symptoms as defined above may
             participate in the study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
